methods.clearScriptPathLoader: Removes the currently configured script path loader from this script.
methods.evaluateScript:
Evaluates the script and manages liveness of objects that are exported to the user. This method should be called
 from the serial executor as it manipulates static state.

*Overload 1*  
  :param script: (java.lang.String) - the code to execute
  :return: (io.deephaven.db.util.ScriptSession.Changes) the changes made to the exportable objects
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param script: (java.lang.String) - the code to execute
  :param scriptName: (java.lang.String) - an optional script name, which may be ignored by the implementation, or used improve error
                     messages or for other internal purposes
  :return: (io.deephaven.db.util.ScriptSession.Changes) the changes made to the exportable objects
methods.getVariable:

Retrieve a variable from the script session's bindings.

*Overload 1*  
  :param name: (java.lang.String) - the variable to retrieve
  :return: (java.lang.Object) the variable
  
*Overload 2*  
  Note: Java generics information - <T>
  
  :param name: java.lang.String
  :param defaultValue: T
  :return: (T) the value of the variable, or defaultValue if not present
methods.getVariableNames:
Retrieves all of the variable names present in the session's scope

:return: (java.util.Set<java.lang.String>) an unmodifiable set of variable names
methods.getVariables:
Retrieves all of the variables present in the session's scope (e.g., Groovy binding, Python globals()).

:return: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>) an unmodifiable map with variable names as the keys, and the Objects as the result
methods.hasVariableName:
Check if the scope has the given variable name

:param name: (java.lang.String) - the variable name
:return: (boolean) True iff the scope has the given variable name

methods.sanitizeThrowable:
If this script session can throw unserializable exceptions, this method is responsible for turning those
 exceptions into something suitable for sending back to a client.

:param e: (java.lang.Throwable) - the exception to (possibly) sanitize
:return: (java.lang.Throwable) the sanitized exception
methods.scriptType: :return: (java.lang.String) a textual description of this script session's language for use in messages.

Sets the scriptPathLoader that is in use for this session.

methods.setUseOriginalScriptLoaderState:
Informs the session whether or not we should be using the original ScriptLoaderState for source commands.

:param useOriginal: (boolean) - whether to use the script loader state at persistent query initialization
:return: boolean
methods.setVariable:
Inserts a value into the script's scope.

:param name: (java.lang.String) - the variable name to set
:param value: (java.lang.Object) - the new value of the variable
methods.unwrapObject:
Asks the session to remove any wrapping that exists on scoped objects so that clients can fetch
 them. Defaults to returning the object itself.

:param object: (java.lang.Object) - the scoped object
:return: (java.lang.Object) an obj which can be consumed by a client
